Author: pixcavator
Content: These suggestions resemble a lot the advice given to new assistant professors on how to find time for research among all the teaching, committees, etc. Strange to find it here... But #4 is very relevant (no offense YC News!).

Author: danw
Content:
So many great quotes and insights from this article:

"I hate being called a college dropout. It's like almost 10 years ago already. And I didn't drop out, I just decided to learn on my own.", "i didn't drop out, i got kicked out, get it straight"

"I think it's underestimated how much work we put into it. Our success wasn't random - we work non-stop."

"Fact: The best ideas come from the bathroom."

"When i was out [in Silicon Valley,] every person i met gave me a business card that said CEO. It just seems like everyone is so up in each other's kool-aid they forget to just stfu and work."
